{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSConnectionProtocol"]]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSConnectionProtocol\/set(requireCloseNotify:)"},"metadata":{"externalID":"s:3GIO21TLSConnectionProtocolPAAE3set18requireCloseNotifyySb_tF","roleHeading":"Instance Method","symbolKind":"method","extendedModule":"GIO","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"set","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"requireCloseNotify","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","text":"Bool"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"title":"set(requireCloseNotify:)","role":"symbol"},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"set","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"requireCloseNotify"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In some protocols, the application will know whether or not the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"connection was closed cleanly based on application-level data","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(because the application-level data includes a length field, or is"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"somehow self-delimiting); in this case, the close notify is","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"redundant and sometimes omitted. (TLS 1.1 explicitly allows this;"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in TLS 1.0 it is technically an error, but often done anyway.) You"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_tls_connection_set_require_close_notify()"},{"type":"text","text":" to tell "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"conn"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to allow an “unannounced” connection close, in which case the close"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"will show up as a 0-length read, as in a non-TLS"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketConnection","isActive":true},{"text":", and it is up to the application to check that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the data has been fully received."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that this only affects the behavior when the peer closes the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"connection; when the application calls "},{"code":"g_io_stream_close()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" itself"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"on ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"conn"},{"type":"text","text":", this will send a close notification regardless of the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"setting of this property. If you explicitly want to do an unclean","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"close, you can close "},{"code":"conn","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"’s ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSConnection"},{"text":" rather","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"than closing "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"conn"},{"type":"text","text":" itself, but note that this may only be done when no other"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"operations are pending on "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"conn"},{"type":"text","text":" or the base I\/O stream."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/tlsconnectionprotocol\/set(requireclosenotify:)"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Sets whether or not ","type":"text"},{"code":"conn","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" expects a proper TLS close notification","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"before the connection is closed. If this is ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"type":"text","text":" (the default),"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"then ","type":"text"},{"code":"conn","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will expect to receive a TLS close notification from its"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"peer before the connection is closed, and will return a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"eof","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" error if the connection is closed without proper","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"notification (since this may indicate a network error, or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"man-in-the-middle attack)."}],"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/TLSConnectionProtocol/set(requireCloseNotify:)":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"set","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"requireCloseNotify"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSConnectionProtocol\/set(requireCloseNotify:)","type":"topic","title":"set(requireCloseNotify:)","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Sets whether or not "},{"code":"conn","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" expects a proper TLS close notification","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"before the connection is closed. If this is "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" (the default),"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"then ","type":"text"},{"code":"conn","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will expect to receive a TLS close notification from its"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"peer before the connection is closed, and will return a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"eof"},{"type":"text","text":" error if the connection is closed without proper"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"notification (since this may indicate a network error, or"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"man-in-the-middle attack).","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/tlsconnectionprotocol\/set(requireclosenotify:)"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/SocketListener":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketListener","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/socketlistener","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"A "},{"code":"GSocketListener","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is an object that keeps track of a set","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"of server sockets and helps you accept sockets from any of the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"socket, either sync or async."}],"title":"SocketListener","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SocketListener"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SocketListener"}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/TLSServerConnection":{"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSServerConnection","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"TLSServerConnection","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"TLSServerConnection","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/tlsserverconnection","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"TLSServerConnection","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"code":"GTlsServerConnection","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is the server-side subclass of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[class","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSConnection"},{"text":"], representing a server-side TLS connection.","type":"text"}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/TLSClientConnection":{"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/tlsclientconnection","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSClientConnection","title":"TLSClientConnection","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"TLSClientConnection","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"TLSClientConnection","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTlsClientConnection"},{"type":"text","text":" is the client-side subclass of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[class","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSConnection"},{"text":"], representing a client-side TLS connection.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/SocketConnection":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SocketConnection","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SocketConnection","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketConnection","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/socketconnection","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSocketConnection"},{"type":"text","text":" is a [class"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOStream","isActive":true},{"text":"] for a connected socket. They","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"can be created either by [class"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketClient","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"] when connecting to a host,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"or by [class","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketListener","type":"reference"},{"text":"] when accepting a new client.","type":"text"}],"title":"SocketConnection"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/IOStream":{"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/iostream","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOStream","title":"IOStream","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"IOStream","kind":"identifier"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"IOStream"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GIOStream"},{"type":"text","text":" represents an object that has both read and write streams."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Generally the two streams act as separate input and output streams,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"but they share some common resources and state. For instance, for"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"seekable streams, both streams may use the same position."}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/SocketClient":{"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SocketClient"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketClient","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSocketClient"},{"type":"text","text":" is a lightweight high-level utility class for connecting to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"a network host using a connection oriented socket type."}],"title":"SocketClient","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/socketclient","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SocketClient"}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/TLSConnectionProtocol":{"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/tlsconnectionprotocol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSConnectionProtocol","title":"TLSConnectionProtocol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"TLSConnectionProtocol"}],"fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"TLSConnectionProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GTlsConnection"},{"type":"text","text":" is the base TLS connection class type, which wraps"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a [class","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOStream","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"] and provides TLS encryption on top of it. Its","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"subclasses, [iface"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSClientConnection"},{"type":"text","text":"] and"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[iface"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSServerConnection","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"], implement client-side and server-side TLS,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"respectively."}],"type":"topic","role":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/TLSConnection":{"role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/tlsconnection","abstract":[{"code":"GTlsConnection","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is the base TLS connection class type, which wraps"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"a [class"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/IOStream","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"] and provides TLS encryption on top of it. Its","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"subclasses, [iface"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSClientConnection","isActive":true},{"text":"] and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[iface"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TLSServerConnection","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"], implement client-side and server-side TLS,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"t